cs.LO, cs.IT, cs.PL, cs.GT, cs.CC

The paper discusses the prospects for a fundamental theory of information that incorporates qualitative and structural aspects, which suggests it could belong to the Logic (cs.LO), Information Theory (cs.IT), Programming Languages (cs.PL), Game Theory (cs.GT), or Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-categories. The paper specifically mentions Domain Theory, Dynamic Logic, and Process Algebra, which are all related to Logic and Programming Languages. It also discusses Game Semantics and Geometry of Interaction, which are related to Game Theory and Computational Complexity. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LO, cs.IT, cs.PL, cs.GT, and cs.CC, in that order.
